                    <span>Do we have a National Identity? Can't a National Identity change over time?  If we didn't expect our nation to change over time, then the constitution would not have permitted the amendment process. 
<br />
<br />Disccusing all sides of what makes up our National Identity and our cultural values is important.  We do not want to forget who we were nor who we are.  Perhaps it is important to remember from a biologist's point of view we are all "Out of Africa"
<br />
<br />This book begins the discussion and evokes much thought. America is what America chooses to be.  </span>
                  
