                    <span>Anyone arguing that the Founders' intent was for the US to be Christian anything is a revisionist. This nation is not founded on Christianity in any way. The Founders said it themselves repeatedly, were very public about the basis for American values, which obviously everyone else agreed with. It does not take a degree in history, or even a high school diploma, to know what the Founders intended. Anyone can literally just ask them. Their words, written and from speechs, are publically available.</span>
                  
              
